The paper deals with privacy concerns in the collection of user location data, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a methodology for analyzing mobility data, which involves data processing and modeling, making it relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of real-world datasets and the development of a mobile app prototype suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper's focus on time series modeling and prediction suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
